{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f9836854-1e2c-458b-a6ec-950d6f696900","content":"I found several issues with this `template.json` file:\n\n1. **Missing required field**: `identity` is required but not present.\n2. **Invalid datatype**: `\"invalid-type\"` on line 9 is not a valid datatype. Valid values include: `bool`, `choice`, `float`, `int`, `hex`, `text`, `string`.\n3. **Missing `sourceName`** (optional but typically expected): Without it, the template won't perform any name replacements during instantiation.\n\nThe file also uses a minimal structure that's technically incomplete — the `shortName` `\"build\"` may conflict with existing .NET templates, and there's no `identity` field which is required by the .NET template engine to uniquely identify the template.\n\n**Minimum fix** — add `identity` and fix the datatype:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"author\": \"Test\",\n  \"classifications\": [\"Test\"],\n  \"identity\": \"Test.Template\",\n  \"name\": \"Test Template\",\n  \"shortName\": \"build\",\n  \"symbols\": {\n    \"myParam\": {\n      \"type\": \"parameter\",\n      \"datatype\": \"string\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5088079f-3843-490f-b428-ca452de816fd","outputTokens":275,"requestId":"500A:99ACC:31B3BCF:363E040:69FBE1DF"},"id":"d477dc44-3556-4000-88bd-aeddd67e3d3d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:50:47.406Z","parentId":"abbfde0f-2fcb-4eab-8ae9-f05e920d2298"}
